{
  "texts": [
    "The attack causes the dosing pump to release HCl even when no water is pumped 3.",
    "However, due to pH sensor AIT201, this attack is detected.",
    "Further, if we assume that AIT201 is also spoofed to show normal range of measurements -a redundant downstream sensor AIT501 incorporated in P5 is able to detect the abnormality in pH.",
    "However, if AIT501 is also spoofed, it may not be able to detect the attack from the measurements made.",
    "As a side effect, changing the pH might possibly change its conductivity sensor reading, permitting the attack to be detected."
  ]
}